  "decision_conditions": [
    "<div><span arial=\"\" style=\"\">The proposed development in regards to its design and sitting would present as an uncharacteristic addition to the original dwelling, the terrace row, and the wider area. Marsh Green Road is characterised by its singular hipped roofscape. The introduction of a hip-to-gable roof extension would detract from the&nbsp;</span>uniformity of the hipped roofscape in the surrounding context. The proposed gabled roof would present a conflicting and visually jarring roofscape. The gabled roof would be visible from the street scene, noting the application site's prominent position at the end-of-terrace. The gabled roof would disrupt the symmetry, uniformity, and rhythmical nature of the terrace rows along Marsh Green Road and their shared, singular, hipped roofscape. The hip-to-gable extension would imbalance the terrace row and would not reflect the other end-of-terrace dwelling.&nbsp;As such, the proposed development is contrary to:<br></div><div><br></div><div><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nNational Planning Policy Framework </span>National Planning Policy Framework\r\n(NPPF) (DLUHC, 2023)<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- Policy D4 of the\r\nLondon Plan (March 2021)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- Policy\r\nCP3 of the </span>Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy (July 2010)<o:p></o:p></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nPolicies BP8 and BP11 of the </span>Local Development Framework (LDF) Borough\r\nWide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011)<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">- The Residential\r\nExtensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \" pt=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\">-\r\nPolicies SP2, DMD1 and DMD6 of </span>The London Borough of Barking and\r\nDagenhamâ€™s Draft Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Submission Version, December 2021)<o:p></o:p></p></div>"
